pull.title: p2p: Remove dead code for nVersion=10300
pull.body: This code is undocumented and confusing as well as dead, since peers with a version that old are disconnected immediately.

events.message: p2p: Remove dead code for nVersion=10300

events.body:
utACK fa5099c
Looks like the final place in the code checking for that version is in walletdb:
https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/0738b88fe0b6c840e3cefa810c2b6de6c8b32ed0/src/wallet/walletdb.cpp#L473

utACK fa5099ceb757c9d56fa54a08d0441750df6c8869

If you felt like it you could also remove a bunch of additional code from the `msg_version` class in `test_framework/messages.py` since the test framework won't work for anything older than a release or two ago. You could remove the `if self.nVersion >= 106` and `if self.nVersion >= 209:` conditionals.
